  "prompt": "What is \"Midwest\"?",
  "response": "The term \"Midwest\" refers to a geographic and cultural region in the United States, traditionally considered to comprise states located in the north-central part of the country. The exact definition of the Midwest can vary, but it generally includes states such as:\n\n- Illinois\n- Indiana\n- Iowa\n- Kansas\n- Michigan\n- Minnesota\n- Missouri\n- Nebraska\n- North Dakota\n- Ohio\n- South Dakota\n- Wisconsin\n\nSome definitions may also include parts of other states, such as parts of Kentucky, West Virginia, and Pennsylvania.\n\nThe Midwest is known for its diverse landscape, which includes prairies, forests, and lakes. Economically, it has a rich agricultural history and is often associated with farming and rural communities. Major cities in the Midwest include Chicago, Detroit, Minneapolis-St. Paul, and St. Louis. Culturally, the region has a blend of influences, with a mix of urban and rural traditions, which contribute to its unique identity.",
